# Run app
1. To run app, run `yarn start` and go localhost:3000

# Deploy on github pages
before redeploy to github pages, change homepage to:
    "homepage": "http://emeraldtanmeiing.github.io/random-people-display",

To redeploy app to github pages, do:
    0. change settings in package.json
        "homepage": "http://emeraldtanmeiing.github.io/random-people-display",
    1. merge code to local master branch
    2. push to remote master branch
    3. run `npm run deploy` in terminal
    4. go live site to check changes: http://emeraldtanmeiing.github.io/random-people-display
    note that it may takes few minutes to reflect changes
    
# Deploy on heroku
before redeploy to heroku, change homepage to:
    "homepage": "https://random-people-display.herokuapp.com/",

2. To redeploy app to github pages, do:
    0. change settings in package.json
        "homepage": "https://random-people-display.herokuapp.com/"
    1. merge code to local master branch
    2. push to remote master branch
    3. open powershell in directory
    4. run `git add .`, `git commit -m "description"
    5. run `git push heroku master`
    6. run `heroku open`
    7. go live site to check changes: https://random-people-display.herokuapp.com/random-people-display
    note that it may takes few minutes to reflect changes